caption: Not really a restaurant, more like Nathan's on the boardwalk, but you have to do most of the service yourself and pay restaurant prices, tip included in your check, for mainly greasy but good food and expensive cocktails in plastic cups, disposable everything (but PC "compostable"). Owners figured out how to use pandemic to get rid of staff and charge suckers as though they were in a restaurant.

Cute spot. Went for brunch. Liked the backyard seating and the set up they have for Covid. Food was good, too. Their pancake tasted like a KFC biscuit. The drinks were expensive though. No drink specials.
DELICIOUS! I'd be there 2-3 times a week if I lived close...🤤

We try to support local restaurants and businesses as much as possible, and are aware that service can be slower during these times. Also must say that we are extremely patient people. We arrived around 11:30 and sat on the back patio. At the time we arrived, only 3 other tables were filled. We received our beverages but after about an hour our food was not yet brought out. Other tables who sat after us received their food as well. Finally a waitress came over after passing us by time and time again and said the food would be next. Still after that other tables got their food and after 1 hour and twenty minutes we still did not receive our food and tried to leave. I’m just disappointed that no one came out or even paid attention to us sitting there for that long without food. I love court street grocers but I will never come to hihi again.
Awesome drinks!

Staff turned the lights off on us early while we were still drinking outside. I understand employees want to go home if it’s slow but it was only 9:15. Would have just left a bad tip but already tipped 20% through their mobile ordering system. Leaving a bad review instead. Already hard to support businesses when you’re forced to eat outside in the cold.
Stop what you’re doing and order a burger right now.
Loved the place. Has an outside patio in the backyard with cozy heaters. Excellent customer service. Food is also amazing for the prices.

Great burger and chicken sandwich for a night in! Everything arrived hot and the fries were even still crispy. Excellent customer service, as well - On a busy Friday evening they included an extra beverage to apologize for the delay. Not necessary, but super appreciated!
Heated Patio is the best!!! Super friendly staff and of course amazing food!!!
The best Muffaletta north of Lake Pontchartrain.

Hi Hi Room was rocking the delivery today.  Love it.  Had a cardiac special: sliders and fried chicken (only once in a blue moon).  Execution on both was flawless.  Sliders: crispy griddled beef, american cheese, sweetness of chopped grill onions, pickle on a potato bun - its a much much better version of the classic white castle slider.  However, one thing, they should slap some of that ridiculously good Hi HI sauce on it (sauce that comes from the fried chicken).  Fried chicken was flawless: partially boned thighs, crispy skin, nice brined taste, not greasy, awesome.  Don't forget the fine and flaky, buttery biscuits.  Makes me want to be Earl in the movie Diner, the guy who ate the entire left side of the menu.....
Incredible food, great service

Agree with the reviews below that food is just okay, pricey for what it is, chicken wings were undersauced/seasoned, drinks were pricey and too sweet, and warning that ‘Mixto’ is served cold, because the menu should probably say it when it’s late October and it’s long past cold soup season. Would recommend the sliders or CSG sandwich, but you could go to Shake Shack or CSG for them.  Interesting food idea, but not elevated enough from the food that inspires it to make it worth the trip or price.

I had a great time at the HiHi room. The backyard patio was cozy yet spacious. The staff has taken all the proper safety procedures.  I ordered the spicy fried chicken and it was incredible! It was the perfect level of crispy and juiciness while being slightly spicy. The beak came along with two small delicious buttery biscuits.  They also have a great drink selection, i ordered an Other Half beer.
Pricy but delicious
Decent food, too expensive for what you get though
I love their revised menu (especially the sliders, both the burgers and the breakfast sliders). They've also got one of the best backyard patios in Brooklyn.
Restaurant with a retro vibe owned by the same folks that own Court Street Grocers. One of the best burgers in Brooklyn. Great, spacious backyard.

This dining experience was great from the moment that I arrived we were greeted with warm smiles, then directed to outdoor backyard seating. (Social distancing of course) I choose the sliders with fries, great comfort food choice. The chef came and served us personally, thanks Sandy!!! Sandy served us and explained the beautiful salad which has an Asian flare. The potato salad was just right, not mushy. This whole dining experience was great with great service and hospitality.  See you again HI HI ROOM...

Fun menu that’s both nostalgic and inventive. Loved the sliders and pineapple whip, which I enjoyed in the Fern Garden (a real gem of a backyard, such an oasis!!). Service was warm and welcoming. This is a great addition to Smith Street and I can’t wait to try everything on the menu!

The back garden at this place has been a life saver. They have a canopy that can extend or retract so it is always perfect for any weather, as we have to dine outdoors.  The food is also solid and the Mobile ordering is super convenient, plus as a result no waiting for the check, when it’s time to go you can just leave.  I personally am fond of the pineapple whip that stuff is great, and on top of a cocktail, perfect on a hot day!
Tasty food and large portions! The pineapple sole drink is spectacular!
Sliders are excellent and their lazy riverita and wail call cocktails are very tasty. Love the backyard
Amazing service and super COVID friendly. Check out the back yard!
Solid effing everything. I ❤️ HIHI
Really fun diner vibe! The burger may look slightly intimidating, but you’re worth it 🍔 😉

A fancy diner. Nothing incredible. The food is fair at best. The beverage program could use work. Drinks were unbalanced and overly sweet for my taste and a little light on the pour. Don’t need to revisit.

I went to this spot because I've been going to CSG for sandwiches for years. They know what they're doing, but still, a restaurant is a different venture. They nailed it. Everything was delicious and the service was great. Crab salad app was awesome, also the oysters. I had the Cincinnati spaghetti thing with duck chili, really delicious. I had the serrano tequila cocktail and some red wine with dinner, all excellent.

Excellent food and service. Appreciated how attentive the bartenders were even though we were doing dry January!  We got the burger, shrimp and grits and the boiled peanuts - all were incredible! We will be back again!
Good food

I had the burger and it was good, but very expensive for what it was. I really like the decor, but the space is crammed, and I can't enjoy the time there with so many people touching elbows and the room being loud. I think I might prefer it during the slow time. Service at the bar is friendly, but really slow.
Kid friendly neighborhood spot with great service and vibe but food-wise falls a little short of the hype
Great food; smart, friendly service; thoughtfully designed, cheerful space.

Food was was above average, service was below par - by a long shot.  Sat down to a nice high top around 11:15 am, 11:35 am still no one had come by our table.  This was odd only because it seemed like there were a decent amount of workers. After asking the hostess, she informed us that someone called out sick and the floor manager would be helping us.  We thought, okay - cool, totally get it - should have a better experience now.  Wrong. Just took far to long to address the issue and did little to help our table.  Food was good, I would go back for the food.  Drinks were expensive.

We stopped in at HiHi for Sunday brunch around 11:00.  The staff were really helpful and welcoming. We had the O’Brien’s Sausage and Californian sandwich both of which were excellent and one of the best bloody Marys I’ve had.  A really good little place just off the beaten track in Brooklyn with excellent, friendly staff. The guy who served us at the bar, Steven, was especially good - many thanks :)  Would thoroughly recommend :)

The food was incredible for brunch. Super tasty and filling. The cocktails were also really fun and yummy. The dining room was cute and seemed like it would be a fun date spot. The backyard wasnt open yet but I want to return to check it out. Our server was also really nice and attentive.
the crab meat burger special was amazing! great atmosphere, our server was friendly. skip the coffee

In short - incredible food, fun vibe.  I came here because I had read it was opened by the same people who own Court Street Grocers, my favorite sandwich spot in NYC, and boy it did not disappoint. It has a funky hip vibe, well lit with light wood and green leather chairs and booths, a sculpture of a whale fighting a kraken on a wall, you know, the staples.  The pea soup was great, not too thick with a nice texture created by a good scattering of ingredients: bacon bits, burrata, other stuff I'm not subtle enough to identify.  Then I had the muffaletta, and oh my god delicious. The last muffaletta I had was in New Orleans and this gives it a run for its money - fluffy thick bread, stack of meats that makes a muffaletta, and wow the olive and sauce situation was a perfect complement.  The staff were friendly and attentive, I had a great time.  Definitely recommend!
white fish white fish white fish!

I love this addition to the neighborhood. First the food is good, burger is a fantastic so get it. I cannot wait to go back and try more. Everything that came out of the kitchen looked awesome. The real sleeper star here is the wine list that carries the who’s who of American natural wine and some big hitters from Europe all priced really well.

Though they had a weird (menu-wise) ramp up, the Hi Hi has rapidly become one of my favorite neighborhood spots.  The place is beautifully bright and lively, and their burger....  my god, their burger.
very basic cooking foods, no one dish can be impressive
Very ordinary boring food, you can get the same level of food in nine of the ten nearby restaurants, I think this place is just a marketing, you will get the same food at costco ...

Burger, spaghetti Cincinnati (gotta request extra Parmesan cheese), and boiled peanuts are all great - awesome value for good food. Wonderful service. Decor is a bit quirky but hey, good for a date night
Fun atmosphere, great service, and really tasty food. Unique takes on classic fare, with excellent drinks.
Delightful neighborhood gem
Great place for fun night out. We had the burger and the curry vegetables both were good! Cocktails were also good and the service was friendly and helpful!
Best cheeseburger in town

We had a good time here.  Pros - Great food. Flavorful, mixed menu, fun signatures like Spaghetti Cincinnati (high-brow Skyline Chilli) - Cool interior. Much more energetic than previous restaurants in the space. Somehow they've made the bar area feel a lot more open and welcoming. - Back Garden. It's winter as I write this but excited to see what they do with the space, was great when previous restaurants occupied this space.  Cons - Really loud. Hopefully, they might end up fixing this with acoustic tiles or something. Kind of a good problem for them to have, I don't think previous restaurants ever had this many people in them. - A little pricey. I would say it's a little pricey but they are elevating things like the burger, it's not just a regular burger so it seems fair.  A great start overall considering they've only been open for a month.

The burger was one of the best I've had. Classic fries. They had a Threes Brewing IPA on tap which was nice. Ate at the bar and had great service from our very kind and personable hipster bartender. Will be back for the Cincinnati chili- I CAN'T WAIT!!
Generous Warm Place - Killer Trout
Went for lunch in opening day. The California Classic sandwich sounded way simpler than it tasted — very delicious and satisfying. Staff was welcoming. Will try dinner there soon.

I love the makeover of this restaurant space! It's l bright and eclectic and chill. I'm excited to have it on Smith Street! It's always a win when people who running successful businesses in the neighborhood open more!  We popped in for lunch and enjoyed our burger and the Jonah crab salad (the avocado was mottled in an unappetizing manner, but I cut those bits off). The staff was really nice and it's good to see them doing a brisk daytime business. I had a peek at the dinner menu and will definitely be in to work my way through that. Most exciting is that it's open for breakfast which is a very welcome addition to this part of Boerum Hill.
AVOID! Food was really poor, the fennel sausage was horrible. If you're a fan of undercooked chicken however this may be the place for you..  Service also left a lot to be desire.
Excellent food and service!

Had an excellent meal here! Ambiance and drinks were stellar. The whitefish and accompanying waffles were great, the salads superb, but my favorite was the Spaghetti Cincinnati. Dense, chewy pasta doused liberally with fancy duck chili. So good. I could eat it for breakfast, lunch, and dinner.
Exceptional! The Whitefish was revelatory! I can't wait to go back!
Incredibly smooth brunch cocktails and probably the best shrimp and grits you’ll ever have (the secret: chilis, why not?).
Oh HiHi Mark! An Oscar-worthy ROOM, crew, and catering.
